The Durban Festival of Chariots was held over the Easter Weekend at the old Durban Drive Inn. Thousands of visitors were treated to food, fashion, dance and drama extravaganza. The traditional chariot parade that took place on Good Friday and Easter Monday saw devotees pull the chariots through the streets of Durban. Krsangi Radhe Dasi said that this was the 30th Durban Festival of Chariots and ISKCON put on a bigger and better event with many new features. Free vegetarian meals were served to all.